I deleted all trash from work computer, cleaned it with CCleaner and reboot. Then I installed TortoiseHG 2.3.1. Switch on mercurial_keyring. Still crash on command "hg pull". So it is a problem exactly on my work PC. I showed it to our Admin. He finds a solution - to use bat-file hg.bat:
{{{
runas /savecred /user:vosipov@fastlane.local "hg %*"
}}}

It says that problem in Windows UAC. Though I am admin, when I launch "hg pull" the UAC sometimes doesn't know that I am admin. When launch hg from my account with the command "runas /savecred /user:vosipov@fastlane.local "hg pull"" then no crash. It uses ntdll.dll which works under system SID and which uses hg which runs under users SID.

