The issue with getting different scan modes when reading in the same file twice is an issue in RSL not Py-ART.  For example:

``` C 
#include "rsl.h"

void main(int argc, char **argv) {

    Radar *radar;
    
    RSL_print_version();

    // read the file, print the scan_mode, 0: PPI, 1: RHI
    radar = RSL_uf_to_radar("RAW_NA_000_025_20130606030822");
    printf("scan_mode: %i\n", radar->h.scan_mode);
    RSL_free_radar(radar);
    
    // re-read the file and print scan mode
    radar = RSL_uf_to_radar("RAW_NA_000_025_20130606030822");
    printf("scan_mode: %i\n", radar->h.scan_mode);
}
```

Produces:
```
$ ./a.out 
RSL version v1.47.
scan_mode: 1
scan_mode: 0
```

I'll let Bart Kelley know about this issue and see if there is a fix.

