There are other problems with using `valid_data` after failed deserialization. There is no way to know if the partial results are otherwise valid without running the whole thing through the schema validation again. Also, the transformed output might not be considered valid input. In this example the members key could be missing or the value could be something other than a list. You might need to relax the team schema and validate the members in a second pass.

```py
class TeamSchema(Schema):
    members = fields.Nested(fields.Dict, many=True)

    @post_load
    def ignore_invalid_members(self, data):
        loaded_users = [UserSchema().load(user_data) for user_data in data['members']]
        data['members'] = [user.data for user in loaded_users if not user.errors]
        return data
```

